[resource]
script = ExtResource("3_hc28f")
id = "add_node_from_class"
title = "Add node from class"
description = "**Purpose**
Add a new node instance to an existing Godot scene based on a specific class.

**Usage notes**
- The `scene_path` parameter specifies which scene to modify.
- The `node_class` parameter determines the type of the new node.
- The `node_name` parameter sets the name for the new node instance.
- The `parent_path` parameter specifies where in the scene hierarchy to add the node. The scene root node path is \".\". For example:
  - Node2D (path \".\")
    - Child1 (path \"Child1\")
      - Grandchild1 (path \"Child1/Grandchild1\")
    - Child2 (path \"Child2\")
- If `parent_path` is omitted, the node will be added to the scene root.

**Example**
scene_path: res://scenes/main_scene.tscn
node_class: CharacterBody2D
node_name: Player
parent_path: Main/CharacterLayer"
category = ExtResource("1_8mx5s")
parameters = Array[ExtResource("2_2p5ws")]([SubResource("Resource_8jokm"), SubResource("Resource_r2eb5"), SubResource("Resource_ctju7"), SubResource("Resource_7n4cx"), ExtResource("4_8meys")])
options = Array[ExtResource("1_kd5x2")]([ExtResource("3_258ut"), ExtResource("4_8qtl3"), ExtResource("5_0s5bk"), ExtResource("6_q1y40")])
